<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-09-10T15:32:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-09-10T15:32:00-05:00" n="441" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d441">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.3412 Anti-War/1: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kaufman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                            Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-09-10T16:00:00-04:32"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            10, 1928—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 4:05
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>41. The Bolivian Government through the Minister of Finance has
                                requested me to ask the Department to use its best course to obtain
                                the adhesion of Paraguay to the multilateral treaty for the
                                renunciation of war,<note n="53" xml:id="d441fn53">See <ref target="#pg_1">pp. 1</ref> ff.</note> since the Bolivian
                                Government thinks that such action would facilitate the settlement
                                of Bolivian-Paraguayan boundary question.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kaufman</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>